   b) Both extracts could reduce high glucose level. Low cellular glucose significantly increased GAPDH phosphorylation via AMP-activated protein kinase (AMPK), triggering SIRT1 activation. This mechanism induced the cell cycle progression by decreasing Rb and cdc2 phosphorylation. High expression of proteins (
